    {
      "id": "e8a90b87_b1234f6d",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 140,
      "message": "Just wondering ... Any reason not to use the following ?\n\n  void processDataUpdatedEventAsync(final String dataspaceName, final String anchorName,\n      final OffsetDateTime observedTimestamp, final String xpath,\n      final Operation operation)\n\nDoes it mean that we could get rid of:\n\n  void processDataUpdatedEventAsync(final Anchor anchor, \n      final String xpath, final Operation operation,\n      final OffsetDateTime observedTimestamp)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2022-02-07 15:39:34.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "6318ce24_0f64bd69",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 140,
      "message": "Yes. When an anchor is deleted, it is not possible to fetch details about schema-set name associated with the anchor. So, in the case of delete, it is required to fetch information before the actual deletion takes place. \n\nIn the old implementation, the anchor details were fetched when the event payload was created, which is too late in the case of anchor delete.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-02-07 15:48:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e8a90b87_b1234f6d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
